      "rationale": "Quantitative comparison metrics applied: mean absolute relative error (MARE), root mean square error (RMSE), and coverage probability of 95% prediction intervals. NIH MARE = 4.2%; velocity RMSE = 2.8% tip speed. Bayesian model validation metric (area validation metric u_val) = 0.12, well within acceptance threshold of 0.25. Statistical equivalence tests pass at α = 0.05 for all primary QoIs."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 5,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/qoi-relevance-mrl5",
      "rationale": "Primary QoI (NIH, normalized index of hemolysis) is the clinically accepted metric per ASTM F1841 and directly maps to the regulatory decision criterion (NIH < 0.1 g/100L). Secondary QoIs (peak shear stress, exposure time distribution, volume-averaged shear rate) are mechanistically linked to hemolysis through the Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law model. QoI-to-decision mapping documented in requirements traceability matrix RTM-2025-001."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
