      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/validation-relevance-mrl5",
      "rationale": "Validation experiments conducted on the identical FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry at COU-identical operating conditions (2.5–6.0 L/min, 2500–4000 RPM). Blood analog fluid (glycerol-water, matched viscosity and density) used with porcine RBCs for hemolysis tests. Geometric fidelity confirmed by CMM inspection of test articles against CAD nominal (all critical dimensions within ±25 µm). Validation domain fully encompasses COU operating space."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 5,
