      "rationale": "Model form uncertainty assessed by comparing three turbulence models (k-omega SST, realizable k-epsilon, RSM) and two hemolysis damage accumulation models (Giersiepen-Wurzinger, Zhang power-law). k-omega SST with Giersiepen-Wurzinger selected based on best agreement with validation data. Model form uncertainty contribution quantified as ±12% of NIH prediction and included in total uncertainty budget. Sensitivity of regulatory decision to model form uncertainty confirmed negligible (all model variants predict NIH < 0.08, well below 0.1 threshold)."
    },
    {
