      "rationale": "All model inputs characterized with probability distributions: fluid viscosity (CV=2.1%), hematocrit (CV=3.0%), pump geometry tolerances (±25 µm per CMM data), inlet velocity profile (derived from upstream piping CFD with uncertainty propagation). Monte Carlo UQ study with N=10,000 samples executed; 95th percentile NIH = 0.072, confirming margin against 0.1 threshold. Input sensitivity analysis (Sobol indices) identifies hematocrit and impeller tip clearance as dominant contributors (S_T > 0.1); all other inputs S_T < 0.03.",
