  "hasDecisionRecord": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/morrison-cou2-mrl5-accepted-2026",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-credibility-assessment-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 13 ASME V&V 40 credibility factors have been assessed and achieve the required level 5 for MRL 5. Structured evidence supports acceptance: (1) Software QA: ISO 9001 QMS verified by independent audit, zero critical findings. (2) Code verification: MMS confirms second-order convergence across all governing equations. (3) Discretization error: GCI < 1.5% for all primary QoIs; asymptotic convergence confirmed. (4) Test conditions: NIST-traceable calibration, ASTM F1841 protocol compliance verified. (5) Output comparison: MARE 4.2% for NIH, Bayesian area validation metric 0.12 (threshold 0.25). (6) QoI relevance: NIH directly maps to regulatory criterion; mechanistic linkage documented. (7) Validation relevance: Identical geometry and COU-spanning operating conditions used. (8) Solver error: Residuals < 1e-6, QoI convergence < 0.001%; time-step independence confirmed. (9) Use error: Independent two-reviewer check completed, zero critical findings. (10) Model form: Three turbulence models compared; uncertainty ±12% NIH, all variants predict NIH < 0.08 vs threshold 0.1. (11) Model inputs: Monte Carlo UQ (N=10,000) gives 95th-percentile NIH = 0.072; Sobol sensitivity identifies dominant inputs. (12) Test samples: Power-analysis-justified n=10 per operating point; CV 6.2%. (13) Input equivalency: All boundary condition parameters verified within ±2% of experimental set points, deviations propagated into UQ. Total uncertainty budget (combined discretization, model form, input, and measurement) yields NIH 95th-percentile upper bound of 0.081, providing 19% margin against the 0.1 regulatory threshold. The credibility evidence chain is complete from foundational bench data through validation results to the regulatory decision. Decision: Accepted.",
    "decidedAt": "2026-04-19T00:00:00Z"
  },
